---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { personSchema } from '../../lib/jsonld';
---
<BaseLayout title="About" description="Michael Linder, Solutions Architect, owner of Strali Solutions e.U., based in Carinthia, Austria." jsonLd={personSchema}>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight md:text-4xl">About</h1>

    <div class="prose mt-10">
      <p>
        I'm Michael Linder, owner of <a href="https://strali.solutions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Strali Solutions e.U.</a>, based in Noetsch im Gailtal, Carinthia, Austria. My day-to-day work is senior solutions architecture, currently as a contractor for an international semiconductor manufacturer, in a setup that people today call "Platform Engineering" or "GitOps", but that I've been building in ever-new incarnations for twenty years.
      </p>
      <p>
        What has changed are the questions we need to ask along the way. AI is not only changing how we develop, but also who is responsible for what a machine decides. Exactly there, between architecture, regulation, and responsibility, lies my second focus: AI Governance and the EU AI Act in the context of DACH enterprises, particularly SMEs.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside of this professional world, I'm a licensed radio amateur (OE8YML), write for oeradio.at, and run a small holiday house in Carinthia.
      </p>

      <h2>Key Facts</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>20+ years in Enterprise IT: from .NET to Cloud to GitOps</li>
        <li>Currently: IT consulting & AI advisory through Strali Solutions</li>
        <li>Contractor: Senior Solutions Architect in the semiconductor industry</li>
        <li>Focus on AI Governance & EU AI Act for DACH SMEs</li>
        <li>Owner of Strali Solutions e.U., Carinthia, Austria</li>
        <li>Radio amateur OE8YML, contributor at oeradio.at</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>This Site</h2>
      <p>
        My personal corner of the internet. I write about things I'm learning, problems I've solved, and occasionally about topics beyond tech.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>
        Best way is <a href="mailto:michael.linder@rednil.at">email</a>. For professional enquiries, reach out via <a href="https://strali.solutions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">strali.solutions</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can also find me on <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/achildrenmile" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a> and <a href="https://github.com/achildrenmile" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
